author: psharples
msg: The string object based on the file path has been converted to URL/URI type syntax.
So instead of File.separator ("\" on windows and "/" on *nix) use "/" as the
path separator of a URI is always "/".  Was causing problems on Windows as the
pattern matcher of string.split() was receiving a single backslash (escape char).
